Class LoadableDetachableAudioAppletModel

java.lang.Object
  org.apache.wicket.model.LoadableDetachableModel<byte[]>
      org.cast.cwm.data.models.LoadableDetachableAudioAppletModel
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, org.apache.wicket.IClusterable, org.apache.wicket.model.IDetachable, org.apache.wicket.model.IModel<byte[]>, IAudioAppletModel
public class LoadableDetachableAudioAppletModel
extends org.apache.wicket.model.LoadableDetachableModel<byte[]>
implements IAudioAppletModel

This is an implementation of IAudioAppletModel that is backed by a Response in the data store. Upon detach, this model will drop all of its data and subsequent loads will look to the datastore.

Note: This model does not make changes to the datastore. Any calls to setObject(byte[]) will create a transient byte[] that must be persisted within that request. You an access the backing datastore response via #getMResponse().
